100 grams Smoked Salmon
2 unit(s) Brioche Rolls
1 unit(s) Carrot
1 sachet(s) Aioli
1 sachet(s) Crispy Onions
to taste Salt
to taste Pepper
to taste Butter

Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.
Grate the carrot (no need to peel).
Tear the smoked salmon into small pieces. IMPORTANT: Wash hands after handling fish.
Slice the brioche rolls down through the middle (but not all the way through). Butter the bread if you like.
Pop them onto a baking tray and into the oven to warm through, 2-3 mins.
TIP: You can toast your bread in the toaster if you'd like.

Mix the salmon, grated carrot and aioli in a bowl.
Mix well and season to taste with salt and pepper.

Top the bases of the brioche rolls and scatter over the crispy onion. Close the sandwich.
To serve, slice each roll in half widthways.
Divide between plates.